docs.text: Welcome to MkDocs For full documentation visit mkdocs.org . Commands mkdocs new [dir-name] - Create a new project. mkdocs serve - Start the live-reloading docs server. mkdocs build - Build the documentation site. mkdocs -h - Print help message and exit. docs.text: Install a Virtual Environment #1. Install virtual env pip install virtualenv #2. Create a virual environment in the folder of your choice cd your_folder virtualenv name_of_your_virtual_environment #3. Activate your virtual environment source name_of_your_virtual_environment/bin/activate #4 Now you can install pip packages in your virtual environment pip install your_new_package #5. When done, deactivate your virtual environment. You need to be in your_folder directory. deactivate #6. To delete your virtual environment just delete your_folder directory rm -rf name_of_your_virtual_environment #7 To list all your virtual environments lsvirtualenv
